    <exercisegroup>
        <title>Algebraic</title>
        <introduction>
          <p>For the following exercises, write a recursive formula for each arithmetic sequence.</p>
        </introduction>
        <exercise xml:id="PRECALC-Uh8UnDY5Dw-parts" original="PRECALC/modules/m49445/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
          <statement>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li>
                <m>a=\{40,60,80,...\}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>a=\{17,26,35,...\}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>a=\{-1,2,5,...\}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>a=\{12,17,22,...\}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>a=\{-15,-7,1,...\}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>a=\{8.9,10.3,11.7,...\}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>a=\{-0.52,-1.02,-1.52,...\}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>a=\{\frac{1}{5},\frac{9}{20},\frac{7}{10},...\}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>a=\{-\frac{1}{2},-\frac{5}{4},-2,...\}</m>
              </li>
              <li>
                <m>a=\{\frac{1}{6},-\frac{11}{12},-2,...\}</m>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </statement>
          <solution>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li />
              <li>
                <m>a_{1}=17;\ a_{n}=a_{n-1}+9 &amp; n \ge 2</m>
              </li>
              <li />
              <li>
                <m>a_{1}=12;\ a_{n}=a_{n-1}+5 &amp; n \ge 2</m>
              </li>
              <li />
              <li>
                <m>a_{1}=8.9;\ a_{n}=a_{n-1}+1.4 &amp; n \ge 2</m>
              </li>
              <li />
              <li>
                <m>a_{1}=\frac{1}{5};\ a_{n}=a_{n-1}+\frac{1}{4} &amp; n \ge 2</m>
              </li>
              <li />
              <li>
                <m>_{1}=\frac{1}{6};\ a_{n}=a_{n-1}-\frac{13}{12} &amp; n \ge 2</m>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </solution>
        </exercise>
      </exercisegroup>
  
    <exercisegroup>
        <title>Algebraic</title>
        <introduction>
          <p>For the following exercises, write a recursive formula for the given arithmetic sequence, and then find the specified term.</p>
        </introduction>
        <exercise xml:id="PRECALC-Rv63CnzSdW-parts" original="PRECALC/modules/m49445/index.cnxml" license="CC-BY-4.0">
          <statement>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li>
                <m>a=\{7\text{ , }4\text{ , }1\text{ , }...\};</m> Find the 17th term.</li>
              <li>
                <m>a=\{4\text{ , }11\text{ , }18\text{ , }...\};</m> Find the 14th term.</li>
              <li>
                <m>a=\{2\text{ , }6\text{ , }10\text{ , }...\};</m> Find the 12th term.</li>
            </ol>
          </statement>
          <solution>
            <ol marker="(a)" cols="2">
              <li />
              <li>
                <m>a_{1}=4;a_{n}=a_{n-1}+7;a_{14}=95</m>
              </li>
              <li />
            </ol>
          </solution>
        </exercise>
      </exercisegroup>
  
